full_text: U.S. Department of Homeland Security OMB No 1615-0054; Expires 10/31/05 Bureau of Citizenship and Immigration Services Form N-445, Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony AR # A042210183 WSC*000925914 Date October 16, 2003 APPLICANT COPY FADUMA ADEN WARSAME 4322 WEST 176TH ST TORRANCE CA 90504 You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony on: Wednesday, November 12 2003 at: US DISTRICT COURT CENTRAL DISTRICT FAIRPLEX BUILDING 4 POMONA, CA 91768 LOS ANGELES COUNTY FAIRGROUNDS, HALL, * Please report promptly at 12:30 PM M. You must bring the following with you: This letter, WITH ALL OF THE QUESTIONS ON THE OTHER SIDE: ANSWERED IN INK OR ON A TYPEWRITER. Alien Registration Card. Reentry Permit, or Refugee Travel Document. Any Immigration documents you may have. If the naturalization application is on behalf of your child (children), bring your child (children). Other Proper attire should be worn. If you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, you will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must appear at an oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process. (SEE OTHER SIDE) Form N-445 (Rev. 03/26/03)N Page 1
